    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>X-ray spectroscopy technique in which an intense, tunable X-ray beam of variable frequency from a synchrotron radiation source is directed at a sample and the absorption of the X-rays is measured as a function of frequency.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
